    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Before you start cooking, take your <strong>chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Rinse your<strong> brown rice</strong>, add it to a pot with plenty of <strong>cold water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 20-25 min or until it's tender with a slight bite</p><p>Once cooked, drain, return it to the pot and keep covered until serving</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/punchy-peri-peri-double-chicken-with-buttery-brown-rice-and-peas/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your<strong> chicken breast portions</strong> to a chopping board</p><p>Cover with <strong>cling film</strong> and bash with a <strong>rolling pin</strong> until flattened to approx. 1cm thickness</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/punchy-peri-peri-double-chicken-with-buttery-brown-rice-and-peas/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add <strong>most</strong> of your<strong> peri peri spice mix</strong> to a plate (you'll use the rest later!) and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/punchy-peri-peri-double-chicken-with-buttery-brown-rice-and-peas/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Press your <strong>flattened chicken breast portions</strong> onto the plate to evenly coat all over \u2013 this is your <strong>coated chicken</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/punchy-peri-peri-double-chicken-with-buttery-brown-rice-and-peas/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>coated chicken</strong> to the pan and cook for 5-6 min on each side or until browned and cooked through (no pink meat!) \u2013 this is your <strong>peri peri XL chicken</strong></p><p>(Doubled your protein? Use 2 pans!)</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/punchy-peri-peri-double-chicken-with-buttery-brown-rice-and-peas/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Whilst the chicken is cooking, combine your <strong>mayo</strong> with the <strong>remaining peri peri spice mix</strong> and 1/3 of your <strong>cider vinegar </strong>(you'll use the rest later!)</p><p>Add 1/2 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3/4 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[1 tsp]</span> <strong>cold water</strong> and a pinch of <strong>pepper </strong>and stir together \u2013 this is your <strong>peri peri mayo</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/punchy-peri-peri-double-chicken-with-buttery-brown-rice-and-peas/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the rice is cooked, add your <strong>blanched peas</strong> to the pot with a knob of <strong>butter</strong>, your <strong>chicken stock mix</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Stir it all together, cover and leave to stand for 2-3 min or until the peas are warmed through \u2013 this is your <strong>buttery</strong> <strong>rice & peas</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/punchy-peri-peri-double-chicken-with-buttery-brown-rice-and-peas/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Slice the<strong> cooked chicken</strong> finely on a clean board</p><p>Serve the <strong>sliced peri peri XL chicken</strong> with the <strong>buttery</strong> <strong>rice & peas </strong>and your <strong>carrot & cabbage slaw mix</strong> to the side</p><p>Drizzle the <strong>peri peri mayo </strong>over the chicken</p><p>Top the slaw mix with the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>cider vinegar</strong> and drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and season with a pinch of <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
